/ref> ==International career== [[File:Polizoi ArbÃ«ri - Albania U-21 (2).jpg|thumb|upright=1.0|left|Polizoi ArbÃ«ri in action for [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U-21]] in 2009]] ArbÃ«ri was first called up to the [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albanian National U-21 Team]] in April 2008 by coach [[Artan Bushati]]. He was called up along with players also uncapped at U-21 level such as [[ShpÃ«tim MoÃ§ka]] and [[Vilfor Hysa]]. Bushati the players through their paces in [[KamÃ«z]] as they were playing for a place in his U-21 side.<ref>[http://albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=7818&l=a Bushati puts U-21s to the test]</ref>
His first U-21 goal came in a friendly against [[Macedonia national under-21 football team|Macedonia]] at the [[Biljanini Izvori Sports Hall]] in [[Ohrid]] on 19 November 2008. ArbÃ«ri netted the third and final goal for Albania in a 3-0 victory. His goal came in the 80th minute of the game as a result of some excellent play by [[Enco Malindi]] who set up the goal for ArbÃ«ri.<ref>[http://albania-sport.com/mat.php?idm=9734&l=a Albania U-21 destroy Macedonia]</ref> <br clear="all">
